┌─ Summary ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                            │
│  This project provides efficient implementations of various algorithms     │
│  for sampling elements from the general linear group over a finite field.  │
│  The implementations are written in C and rely on FLINT (Fast Library for  │
│  Number Theory) for field arithmetic and linear algebra operations.        │
│                                                                            │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─ Algorithms ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                            │
│  Implementations of the following algorithms to sample from GL(n, q)       │
│  uniformly at random are included.                                         │
│                                                                            │
│    rej                                                                     │
│      a standard rejection sampling method.                                 │
│                                                                            │
│    unrank                                                                  │
│      A novel algorithm based on combinatorial ranking which requires       │
│      only a single integer sampled uniformly at random.                    │
│                                                                            │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─ Usage ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                            │
│  To run the test suite, issue the command `make test`. This will run a     │
│  series of randomized tests for each implemented algorithm.                │
│                                                                            │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
